We are trying to read a comments and find if the track changes are enabled on a large excel document through SAX model

Describe the solution you'd like
We would like to read/open a large Excel file and find the comments in it

Describe alternatives you've considered
We are able to read comments using Open XML DOM model but leads to higher memory demand approx. 9x than original file size.

Additional context

Sample pseudo code below

`using (var reader = OpenXmlReader.Create(spreadSheetDocument.WorkbookPart))
                {
                    while(reader.Read())
                    {
                        Console.WriteLine(reader.ElementType);
                        // Can't the below if be better readable?
                        if (reader?.ElementType == typeof(CommentRangeStart))
                        {
                            // Chance that this is a comment.
                            //CommentRangeStart element = reader.LoadCurrentElement() as CommentRangeStart;
                            //Console.WriteLine($"Comment text {reader.GetText()}, InnerText:{element.InnerText}");
                            result = true;
                        }
                        else if(reader.ElementType == typeof(Deleted)
                              || reader.ElementType == typeof(Inserted)
                              || reader.ElementType == typeof(InsertedRun)
                              || reader.ElementType == typeof(InsertedMathControl)
                              || reader.ElementType == typeof(ParagraphPropertiesChange)
                              )
                        {
                            result = true;
                        }
                    }
                }`

**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
We are trying to read comments of large files and if we use DOM based reading then memory utilization is very high, hence looking a solution with SAX model.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
I would like to read/open large PowerPoint file and find comments in it

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
We are able to read comments using DOM model but its utilizing higher memory approx. 9x than original file size.

**Additional context**
Sample pseudo code as below
`using (var presentationDocument = PresentationDocument.Open(stream, false))
            {
